.TH d2b-launch 1 1970-01-01 d2b "d2b CLI"
.SH NAME
launch \- Launch a trusted configured workload item through its runtime provider
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBlaunch\fR [\fB\-\-item\fR] [\fB\-\-json\fR] [\fB\-\-human\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fITARGET\fR>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Launch a trusted configured workload item through its runtime provider
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-item\fR \fI<ITEM>\fR
Configured launcher item id. Omit to use the declared default or sole item
.TP
\fB\-\-json\fR
Emit a structured JSON result
.TP
\fB\-\-human\fR
Force human\-readable output
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.TP
<\fITARGET\fR>
Canonical workload target or an unambiguous workload id
